# sentimentarcs

PyPI package: `sentimentarcs`  
GitHub repo: `https://github.com/jon-chun/sentiment-arcs`  
Import: `import sentimentarcs`

This version (0.1.2) **installs `unidecode` and `scipy` by default**, so:
- no more clean-text "unidecode not installed" warning
- crux detection and Savitzkyâ€“Golay smoothing work out of the box
